	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On one old TV, the Game Genie code screen displayed improperly, with the image flickering badly and the screen contents not being at the correct position on the screen.  As I recall, the screen was still visible enough to enter code letters (though it wasn't pretty), and once you got past that screen everything was fine.  I've used the NES and Game Genie with several different TVs, and that TV was the only one that exhibited problems (and it was an old model).
<br />
<br />From what I understand about how the PPU outputs composite video, color $0D is the only one that needs to be avoided (not sure if color emphasis changes this or not).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


